        "text": "The drawing-room, as I have before observed, was raised two steps above the dining-room, and on the top of the upper step, placed a yard or two back within the room, appeared a large marble basin, which I recognised as an ornament of the conservatory\u2014where it usually stood, surrounded by exotics, and tenanted by gold fish\u2014and whence it must have been transported with some trouble, on account of its size and weight.",
